The ability to lower into and out of a triple fold is a foundational human movement that demonstrates a baseline capacity at feet, ankles, knees, hips and pelvic control.

Being able to slowly lower into a resting squat position and maintain it for 30 seconds is a powerful master screen for the lower extremity.

Scoring is binary (Y/N) 

While the inability to lower into a resting squat doesn't tell us exactly what isn't functioning, it does tell us that there is a restriction within the lower body system

30 seconds no pain and ability to breathe deeply and calmly

Aspiration: 2 minutes

Prompt:
- Barefoot on hard, flat ground
- Standing hip width apart and feet parallel
- Gradually lower

Qualitative and quantitative scoring

Observations:

